sequenceDiagram
    participant R as Requester
    participant M as Manager
    %% ⚡ CHANGED SECTION
    participant FD as Finance Director
    participant P as Procurement
    participant V as Vendor
    participant F as Finance

    R->>M: Submit purchase request
    M-->>R: PR approved
    %% ⚡ CHANGED SECTION
    Note over M,FD: SOX Control: Spend threshold check ($50,000)
    alt Amount > $50,000
        M->>FD: Route for second approval (SOX segregation of duties)
        FD->>FD: Review spend justification
        FD-->>M: Second approval granted
        M->>P: Forward approved PR (dual approval)
    else Amount ≤ $50,000
        M->>P: Forward approved PR
    end
    P->>V: Issue Purchase Order
    V-->>P: Order confirmation
    V->>F: Submit invoice
    F->>F: 3-way match verification
    F-->>V: Payment processed (NET30)

%% EXPLANATION:
%% Added Finance Director as a new participant. After Manager approval, a spend threshold check (annotated with the $50,000 SOX control note for auditor visibility) routes high-value requests through the Finance Director for a second approval before Procurement receives the PR, while requests at or under $50,000 continue directly to Procurement as before. All existing interactions are preserved unchanged.